AWS SERVICES – FULL PROCEDURE DOCUMENTATION
1. AWS EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud)
Definition

EC2 provides virtual servers in the cloud to run applications.

Steps to Create EC2 Instance

Login to AWS Console

Open EC2

Click Launch Instance

Enter Name:

MyEC2


Choose AMI:

Amazon Linux / Ubuntu / Windows


Instance Type:

t2.micro


Create or select Key Pair

Configure Security Group:

SSH 22
HTTP 80
HTTPS 443


Click Launch Instance

Connect to EC2
ssh -i key.pem ec2-user@Public-IP

2. AWS S3 (Simple Storage Service)
Definition

S3 is object storage for files, backups, and static websites.

Steps to Create S3 Bucket

Open S3

Click Create Bucket

Bucket Name:

mybucket123


Region:

ap-south-1


Click Create Bucket

Upload File

Open bucket

Click Upload

Select file

Click Upload

Enable Static Website Hosting

Open bucket → Properties

Enable Static Website Hosting

Index document:

index.html

3. Elastic Load Balancer (ELB)
Definition

Distributes traffic across multiple EC2 instances.

Steps to Create Load Balancer

Open EC2

Click Load Balancers

Click Create Load Balancer

Choose:

Application Load Balancer


Enter Name:

MyALB


Select VPC and Subnets

Create Target Group

Register EC2 instances

Click Create

4. Elastic Block Store (EBS)
Definition

EBS provides block storage for EC2.

Steps to Create EBS Volume

Open EC2

Click Volumes

Click Create Volume

Select:

gp3


Select Availability Zone

Click Create Volume

Attach EBS to EC2

Select Volume

Click Attach Volume

Select EC2 instance

Mount EBS (Linux)
lsblk
sudo mkfs.ext4 /dev/xvdf
sudo mkdir /data
sudo mount /dev/xvdf /data

5. Auto Scaling
Definition

Automatically increases or decreases EC2 instances based on load.

Steps to Configure Auto Scaling

Create Launch Template

Open Auto Scaling Groups

Click Create Auto Scaling Group

Select Launch Template

Set:

Min: 1
Desired: 2
Max: 4


Attach Load Balancer

Create Scaling Policy

Click Create

6. AWS Lambda
Definition

Serverless compute service to run code without managing servers.

Steps to Create Lambda Function

Open Lambda

Click Create Function

Choose:

Author from scratch


Function Name:

MyLambda


Runtime:

Python 3.x


Click Create

Sample Lambda Code
def lambda_handler(event, context):
    return "Hello from Lambda"

7. AWS Lightsail
Definition

Simplified cloud service for small applications.

Steps to Create Lightsail Instance

Open Lightsail

Click Create Instance

Select OS:

Linux / Windows


Choose Plan

Enter Instance Name

Click Create Instance

8. Amazon CloudWatch
Definition

Monitors AWS resources and applications.

CloudWatch Features

Metrics

Logs

Alarms

Dashboards

Create CloudWatch Alarm

Open CloudWatch

Click Alarms

Click Create Alarm

Select Metric:

EC2 CPU Utilization


Set Threshold:

CPU > 70%


Set Notification

Create Alarm

View Logs

Open CloudWatch

Click Logs

Select Log Group

Summary Table
Service	Purpose
EC2	Virtual server
S3	Object storage
ELB	Traffic distribution
EBS	Block storage
Auto Scaling	Automatic scaling
Lambda	Serverless compute
Lightsail	Simple cloud
CloudWatch	Monitoring
Conclusion

All major AWS core services are successfully explained with procedures.
